cab.content: C.C.60(58) 17th July, 1958 1. Middle East. [Enter A.N., EH. P.M. Still seeking clearance fr. Israel for over-flying. If we canâ€™t get it, operation is impossible. Israel may try to attach conditions. One aircraft went in [& has returned to Cyprus]. Others are held. U.S. have clearance for their opn. : & it is proceeding. First intervention. A.L.B. News is breaking : on tapes and in Press. R.A.B. Awkward situation in H/C. Will have to tell the truth. 2. Parliament. R.A.B. Business for next week.
